===Etymology===
From Old Slavic ''[[bela-]]'' ("white") + ''[[Rus]]'' ("Russia"); The stem [[bela-]] is cognate with [[Baltic]] < Lithuanian [[baltas]] ([[white]]).

===Proper noun===
'''Belarus'''
# A country in Europe. Official name: [[Republic of Belarus]] ([[Рэспублiка Беларусь]]).
